## Infrastructure / Project Hygiene

### Remove spell JSONs from GitHub commit history
> **Dev note:** `backend/data/*.json` files (phb2024_spells.json, spells.json, XGtE_Spells_fixed.json, TCoE_spells.json) were once tracked and are still in git history. Git itself still stores all blob history — `git rm` only stops future tracking. To purge blobs from history requires `git filter-repo --path backend/data/ --invert-paths` (or BFG Repo-Cleaner). This rewrites all commits touching those blobs, requiring a force-push to all branches and every contributor to reclone. **Prerequisite:** ensure the files are in `.gitignore` first. Effort: **Small** (well-defined tooling, but it's a rewrite — confirm before running).

✅ Done — 2026-03-16 — `git-filter-repo --path-glob "backend/data/*.json" --invert-paths --force` run; 52 commits rewritten; force-pushed to GitHub

