## UI — Spell Comparison

### Version / source tags in spell dropdown
> **Dev note:** `SpellCombobox` in `ComparePage.tsx` currently shows level and school badges but not the spell source. The `Spell` model has a `source` CharField (`backend/spells/models.py` line 91). The `Spell` API serializer exposes it. The `Spell` TypeScript type needs `source?: string` added. Dropdown items should add a small source badge alongside `Lvl X` and school badges (e.g. "PHB 2024", "XGtE"). This helps users disambiguate duplicate-named spells from different books. Files: `ComparePage.tsx`, `frontend/src/types/api.ts`. Effort: **Quick win**.

✅ Done — 2026-03-16 — source badge added to selected pill and all dropdown list items

### Source / version filter in spell comparison dropdowns
> **Dev note:** `SpellsPage.tsx` has a `sources` filter backed by `useSpellSources()`. The `SpellFilterBar` inside `ComparePage.tsx` does NOT include a source filter — it only has levels, schools, classes, damage types, and concentration. Add `sources: string[]` to `SpellFilter`, fetch available sources via `useSpellSources()`, and render a `MultiSelect` for it in `SpellFilterBar`. The `applySpellFilter` function already runs client-side against the 1000-spell payload, so no backend changes needed. Files: `ComparePage.tsx`, `frontend/src/hooks/useSpells.ts`. Effort: **Quick win**.

✅ Done — 2026-03-16 — source MultiSelect added to both filter bars; `useSpellSources` wired in

### Bug: Magic Missile shows no damage in spell comparison
> **Dev note:** Root cause — `fix_auto_hit_spells` management command sets `is_auto_hit=True` and `number_of_attacks=3`, and applies `component_flat_modifier=1` to *existing* `DamageComponent` objects. But if the parser extracted zero `DamageComponent` records for a given Magic Missile spell (likely the PHB 2024 version, whose damage text is "1 force damage + your spellcasting ability modifier" with no standard dice pattern), the loop in `SpellAnalysisService` iterates over an empty list and returns `expected_damage=0`. Fix: update `fix_auto_hit_spells` to create a `DamageComponent(dice_count=1, die_size=4, damage_type="force")` if none exist. Affects both the comparison page and the standard analysis endpoint. Files: `backend/spells/management/commands/fix_auto_hit_spells.py`, possibly `backend/analysis/services.py`. Effort: **Quick win**.

✅ Done — 2026-03-16 — `fix_auto_hit_spells` now creates a default `1d4+1 force` `DamageComponent` when none exist; command must be re-run in the container after rebuild

